{"url": "https://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/gallery/james-corden-glamour-awards-2017", "text": "Last night, James Corden picked up Man of the Year at the 2017 GLAMOUR Awards.\n\nGetty Images\n\nHe was presented with the award by Liam Payne, who revealed some very funny stories about his long-time friend.\n\nAdvertisement\n\nDuring his acceptance speech, James thanked GLAMOUR for being the first magazine to interview him and publish his work. The 2010 GLAMOUR Awards was also his first ever presenting gig - the start of an incredible career move which has seen him crack America as the host of The Late Late Show.\n\nIn order to see this embed, you must give consent to Social Media cookies. Open my cookie preferences.\n\nRead next Every time Little Mix's hair and makeup looks were on point Little Mix Every time Little Mix's hair and makeup looks were on point The band that slays together, stays together.\n\n\"I was thinking today that when I hosted this thing, it was the first thing I'd ever hosted in my life. And I remember thinking afterwards, 'I rather enjoyed that', and now that is part of my life and I'm very, very honoured to be back here.\"\n\nHe went on to thank a huge list of women including his wife Julia Carey, his daughter, mum, sister and Gavin & Stacey's Ruth Jones.\n\nJames also spoke about wearing Dior's iconic feminist t-shirt on the cover of GLAMOUR's July 2017 issue.\n\nAdvertisement\n\n\"The truth is, wearing that t-shirt on that magazine, it didn't even occur to me that it would be anything that would even be considered as brave, because I don't think it should be. I long for the day when it isn't a time where we talk about women's rights or equality or any of those things, and it would just be a matter of fact of the world that we're living in.\"\n\n\ud83d\udc4f\ud83d\udc4f\ud83d\udc4f\n\nScroll down for 18 facts we bet you didn't know about James Corden...", "images": ["https://gl-images.condecdn.net/image/0Gp08E7V30Z/crop/405/f/Patrick-stewart-jam